    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"\n",
        "You are HighKeySupps Customer Service & Sales Assistant.\n",
        "\n",
        "You help customers with:\n",
        "1. Order status questions\n",
        "2. Refund and return policy questions\n",
        "3. Product recommendations\n",
        "\n",
        "Be friendly, professional, and concise.\n",
        "Use prior conversation context when relevant.\n",
        "If the question does not fit one of the three categories, politely say you can only help with orders, refunds, and product recommendations.\n",
        "\"\"\""
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ou2V5kxCUb5o"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def router(state: ChatState):\n",
        "    text = state[\"user_input\"].lower()\n",
        "\n",
        "    if any(word in text for word in [\"order\", \"track\", \"tracking\", \"ship\", \"shipping\", \"package\"]):\n",
        "        return {\"intent\": \"order_status\"}\n",
        "    elif any(word in text for word in [\"refund\", \"return\", \"exchange\", \"policy\"]):\n",
        "        return {\"intent\": \"refund_policy\"}\n",
        "    elif any(word in text for word in [\"recommend\", \"suggest\", \"best\", \"protein\", \"pre-workout\", \"caffeine\", \"muscle\"]):\n",
        "        return {\"intent\": \"product_recommendation\"}\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        return {\"intent\": \"unknown\"}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xNIDOfthUeD0"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def order_status_agent(state: ChatState):\n",
        "    user_text = state[\"user_input\"]\n",
        "    history = state.get(\"history\", [])\n",
        "\n",
        "    prompt = f\"\"\"\n",
        "    {SYSTEM_PROMPT}\n",
        "\n",
        "    Conversation history:\n",
        "    {history}\n",
        "\n",
        "    You are the Order Status Agent.\n",
        "    Answer order tracking and shipping questions.\n",
        "\n",
        "    If no order number is provided, ask the user for it.\n",
        "    If an order number is provided, simulate a helpful tracking-style response.\n",
        "\n",
        "    User message: {user_text}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    reply = llm.invoke(prompt).content\n",
        "\n",
        "    updated_history = history + [\n",
        "        f\"User: {user_text}\",\n",
        "        f\"Assistant: {reply}\"\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"response\": reply,\n",
        "        \"history\": updated_history\n",
        "    }"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xfpGLdhKUhiz"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def refund_policy_agent(state: ChatState):\n",
        "    user_text = state[\"user_input\"]\n",
        "    history = state.get(\"history\", [])\n",
        "\n",
        "    prompt = f\"\"\"\n",
        "    {SYSTEM_PROMPT}\n",
        "\n",
        "    Conversation history:\n",
        "    {history}\n",
        "\n",
        "    You are the Refund Policy Agent.\n",
        "    Answer refund, return, and exchange questions.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Use this sample policy:\n",
        "    - Returns allowed within 30 days\n",
        "    - Product must not be heavily used\n",
        "    - Opened items may be eligible only for store credit\n",
        "    - Exchanges are allowed for damaged or incorrect items\n",
        "\n",
        "    If the user says \"it\" or refers to a product indirectly, use the conversation history to figure out what product they mean.\n",
        "\n",
        "    User message: {user_text}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    reply = llm.invoke(prompt).content\n",
        "\n",
        "    updated_history = history + [\n",
        "        f\"User: {user_text}\",\n",
        "        f\"Assistant: {reply}\"\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"response\": reply,\n",
        "        \"history\": updated_history\n",
        "    }"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cHgkUiSPUjVj"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def product_recommendation_agent(state: ChatState):\n",
        "    user_text = state[\"user_input\"]\n",
        "    history = state.get(\"history\", [])\n",
        "\n",
        "    prompt = f\"\"\"\n",
        "    {SYSTEM_PROMPT}\n",
        "\n",
        "    Conversation history:\n",
        "    {history}\n",
        "\n",
        "    You are the Product Recommendation Agent.\n",
        "    Recommend supplements based on the customer's goals.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Product options:\n",
        "    - Whey Protein Isolate: for muscle growth and recovery\n",
        "    - Beginner Pre-Workout: light energy support\n",
        "    - Stim-Free Pre-Workout: for users sensitive to caffeine\n",
        "    - Creatine Monohydrate: for strength and performance\n",
        "\n",
        "    Use the conversation history when the user gives follow-up details like \"I’m sensitive to caffeine.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    User message: {user_text}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    reply = llm.invoke(prompt).content\n",
        "\n",
        "    updated_history = history + [\n",
        "        f\"User: {user_text}\",\n",
        "        f\"Assistant: {reply}\"\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"response\": reply,\n",
        "        \"history\": updated_history\n",
        "    }"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-Nx7H1ODUk7Z"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def fallback_agent(state: ChatState):\n",
        "    user_text = state[\"user_input\"]\n",
        "    history = state.get(\"history\", [])\n",
        "\n",
        "    reply = \"I can help with order status, refund policy, or product recommendations. Please ask about one of those.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    updated_history = history + [\n",
        "        f\"User: {user_text}\",\n",
        "        f\"Assistant: {reply}\"\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"response\": reply,\n",
        "        \"history\": updated_history\n",
        "    }"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Sw6MbnZjUnD6"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "builder = StateGraph(ChatState)\n",
        "\n",
        "builder.add_node(\"router\", router)\n",
        "builder.add_node(\"order_status_agent\", order_status_agent)\n",
        "builder.add_node(\"refund_policy_agent\", refund_policy_agent)\n",
        "builder.add_node(\"product_recommendation_agent\", product_recommendation_agent)\n",
        "builder.add_node(\"fallback_agent\", fallback_agent)"
      ],
